Daily menu of an obese child: don't breakfast and dinner stuffed
Over one third of children between the ages of 9 and 13 have overweight problems, where overweight affects 9 per cent of the school population and obesity affects 5%.
Obese children come from most families with a lifestyle that is not healthy, according to current research.
It is again demonstrated the importance of the environment where it grows for healthy development of the person, as well as the models that serve as reference.
At the table, obsessive children, for example, are fed at least twice as often as children with normal weight.
For dinner, more than 19% of obese had had fried potatoes the day before the analysis, which is linked to the prevention program "obesity is not a coincidence".
In overweight children families there is no custom to practice sports, which is applicable to most current families, where only 15 per cent of children responded that their parents, at least once a week, have time for physical exercise.
Survey of 900 children
The survey was conducted at the end of last year's school year and participated in the same almost 900 basic education children from all over the Czech Republic.
It was already the second edition of the program "obesity is not a coincidence", which supports the General Health Insurance Company and the Unilever company.
So far, more than 12,000 children have participated in the project from 4th to 8th.
An adequate diet and plenty of exercise in the family are determinants, which significantly reduce the number of overweight children and even obesity.
"Only half of the children surveyed have responded that they have five daily meals according to the regime: breakfast, lunch, food, dessert and dinner, which is one of the basic conditions for a healthy diet," he gathers one of the results of the survey.
No breakfast, but with a set for dinner
Experts warn that, in healthy development, details are also important, such as having a fixed time for family breakfast.
In the Czech Republic, however, only 23% of school families have breakfast at the same time.
In most families, each one has a single breakfast.
But the worst thing was to find out that in 10% of households there was no breakfast.
Breakfast, however, is the basis for a proper daily diet.
The study shows that in the families of obese children, fried potatoes are consumed much more often.
Almost all - regardless of weight - drink fresh sweet daily (70%).
Generally, more than 40 per cent of the children surveyed are sports, however, among their parents this result is reduced to less than half, only 15 per cent.
Make Your Diet
The next phase of the study enabled selected horses (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 colleges) to create their own diets from all possible offers according to their tastes and opinions.
"The food preferences of Czech children aged between 12 and 15 years from the point of view of healthy food are far from ideal."
Among its favorite foods are pasta, meat and sweets
"It is especially alarming the popularity of sweet refreshments," warns the final report of the study.
As the main food, the palm is taken by the paste and it follows closely to the bird's flesh.
In practice, children always reject legume and taste for fish and vegetables is very low.
Changes to Healthy Habits
At the same time, the study shows that children are willing to change their eating habits if they receive accurate information.
"In the control group of the participants in the study, who filled the questionnaire after finishing the prevention program "obesity is not an accident", there was in many cases an important change in favor of the principles of healthy food," the study's results point out.
He called attention, for example, to sweet refreshments, where many children would begin to prefer normal and running water.
Children would also choose more frequently in the questionnaire poultry meat and fish for main food and would restrict sweet food consumption and flour derivatives.
