The adventure starts very well.
You are introduced into a story, whose protagonist, Jack, has certain personal problems; to solve them, you are offered to participate in an illegal career throughout America.
You sit on the west coast in San Francisco, and your mission is to get to New York first.
The idea is to offer something interesting.
The route is divided into ten stages and then into more than fifty races.
From this it is shown that each race takes place on a different path and the stages are located in different environments, which are quite diverse and interesting.
Thus, one does not even have the feeling that the game always offers the same.
Some of the environments are even pleasant to see, although the technical level of the graph is equivalent to that of previous series deliveries.
So it's nothing in the other world.
But walking through the desert, the autumn landscape or the high snow-covered mountains produce a very pleasant visual effect.
In addition, the races are diversified from time to time by an atypical element.
So, for example, in the desert you will find a sandstorm that decreases visibility.
On the other hand, in the mountains you have to be careful not to bury an avalanche.
According to that, each race is very well developed.
There's only a couple of models, but that's enough.
For a moment, you try to advance to a number of required rivals (normal in a classic career), then you try to earn time (classic chronic pain) and then you expect a duel against one opponent.
In the middle of all this, the police sometimes appear, which doesn't do but make things even more difficult.
The news is the landscapes outside the car.
Interactive animations are presented when Jack, in most cases, has to escape someone and you have to help him, always pressing the right button at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
It is surprising, however, that there are many less landscapes in the game than I could expect (in particular there are only three).
But the final result is positive, because this element does not get upset and, in the context mentioned above, it is one of the elements that makes the game more interesting.
The driving model follows the traces of the previous episodes.
That means that today is no longer a big thing, but you can't say it's bad.
If you're looking for a realistic simulation, you can look elsewhere.
But a career designed with a lot of action is quite suitable for this driving style, although we can find something better among the competition games.
So far, everything's fine.
But problems arise after a certain time.
Unlike the correct driving models, the same does not happen with collisions.
Of such games you cannot expect to recreate complicated deformations and collisions, but in fact before a hit against any object, you cannot predict how your car will react, with which everything is not in order.
It is typical that when making a very adjusted advance or circulating the car with a normal traffic, there are only slight rocks, but in other almost identical situations, your car ends up making uncontrollable pirates.
The even is completely destroyed.
Thanks to the restorative system, there are no big problems, but it can put you in a bad mood.
The resets are programmed in such a way that when you suffer an accident or get out of the track, the game brings you back to the last rescue point on the track.
However, only five sets are available in each race.
If you consume them all, you have to restart the race from the beginning.
So it's only a help in case something's wrong, but it's not much to trust.
Sometimes, not even the reset helps, it only helps to learn the given stage of memory.
A great disadvantage of the game is that the same facts are repeated in different places.
In some curves, for example, you have to enter in a specific way; otherwise, they are impossible to take.
Sometimes you will find yourself somewhere "civil" vehicles always with the same configuration, even though you are the first, fifths or you arrive five minutes before or after.
This makes you angry especially in situations, when you see two cars going to meet in opposite directions, your opponent goes ahead without problems, but when you get there, you have to turn around or stop.
It's the same when you get here, because it's programmed because the "sudden" will always happen in front of your noses.
The opponents also have another advantage.
During the game you will arrive at places where, regardless of the moment, you will always be promoted by the same opponent in the same place.
In addition, this happens at the end of the game, in a long bridge, which is even more shocking.
Your opponent must arrive before you, at any price.
When he goes in front of you, he makes it difficult for you to see the cars coming forward, so at first you can make the car.
You can understand the idea of creating a game with maximum doses of suspension and adrenaline, but execution is so obvious that it will probably disappoint you soon.
And it's a shame, because even though the travel model is simple, the game is fun and with action, so it's often not possible to follow the details of what happens or where.
And it really doesn't matter, if the merit is taken the idea with fifty exclusive tracks or the ranking in the race so that it doesn't stop boring, or anything else.
An unusual idea is to change cars during the race.
You have to pay attention to the gas outlets next to the road, because right there you have to change your car, although in most cases you will have enough of what you have.
Cars are divided into three categories.
Sports are suitable for urban areas, American strong cars for straight highways and ultra-port exotics for technical driving, for example, by mountain roads with curves.
In addition to the main narrative thread, there is also a series of parallel challenges, i.e. there are races in specific places you will know about the stories.
Here you will get not only medals, but also points of experience for your profile, which serves both challenges and stories.
When reaching the top level, the driver opens up to him several possibilities, beginning with the car and ending with funds for the profile.
At the same time, you have connected an online Autolog function, which compares your results with those of other players and provides other community functions.
One of the most difficult elements to understand is how the last race in history is made.
With the car you get to the metro tunnel (passe), where you put yourself in the dark by the roads (passe).
The speedometer marks you between 150 and 200 km/h (pass) and, suddenly, behind you comes the train from the metro and takes you forward without further notice.
In the editorial we will probably have a discussion about this for several days, about whether during the programming of the game no one thought even a little or if the real authors take us for a panda of fools.
The technical part of the game is nothing extraordinary, but at least the general visual effects result in most of the pleasant cases, sometimes even superlative.
So how sad it is that, at times the most tense, image quality is reduced and, at times, in a serious way.
This affects especially accidents where many participants are involved, when the image quality continues to be invalid.
The sound is good and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In order to please the majority of the youth group, the soundtrack belongs to the category "one of his father and his mother", but it can be assumed that no one would buy the game only for his music.
The final feeling of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore quite confused.
If the game is avoided absolutely stupid errors, we would have trouble asserting that The Run is the best NFS game in recent years.
Gives the feeling that the game is not over.
Entertainment is assured, but prepared because the mistakes will strike you in the eyes with the strength of airport reflectors.
The choirs at the University of Carolina will take part in the "Terciopelo Students" concert.
The joint celebration of the International Student Day and the anniversary of the Third Revolution as a musical experience will take place for the third time at the Festival of Academics.
During the same period, twenty corals from secondary and university centres will be presented.
The festival revolves around two concerts on 17 November.
"The University of Carolina has a high participation in the festival".
Among the current choirs are the Coral of the Faculty of Education and the Faculty of Humanities, the director Václav Hampl is in the festival committee," said the organization's manager, Jakub Čaloun.
The summit of the entire festival is the free entrance for all audiences to the concert of secondary choirs, which will be held on 17 March at 14 hours in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
The program has the participation of the Czech jazzist Karel Rožička and his Celebration Jazz Mass.
The concert "Students of Terciopelo" will be held at the venues of the Municipal House in Vynohrady, where university choirs will participate, including the choir of the University of Carolina.
The Academic Festival aims not only to celebrate the International Students' Day and remember the 22nd anniversary of the Third Revolution, but also to present to the public coral music at the highest level and to promote collaborative creation among young people.
The main organizer is the Czech Coral Union in collaboration with the Jan Kepler Secondary Institute.
All the acts were supported by the mayor of Prague, Bohuslav Svoboda, and the principal of the University of Carolina, Václav Hampl.
The Festival will take place between 16 and 20 November between Prague and Pardubice.
The calendar offers, in addition to the celebrations, a whole series of musical events, improvised performances of students and morning concerts.
More information can be found on the festival website www.festaacademica.cz
