To postpone the change, it was to delay the benefits of digitisation, which involves a decision of public interest, which does not only have a technical dimension, "may cover economic, social, political and national security issues".
These issues, he pointed out, "requires the operation of the entire system established, in accordance with the principle of economic direction of the State, to include a group of attributes that the Constitution leads to the power of the State Executive."
He recalled that a large number of countries around the world have already completed the digital transition, and has done so through the Executive, despite having highly specialized technical bodies.
It cannot be concluded that the Executive, when issuing the contested decree, which in some way invades the area of competence of Congress, as it is providing in the administrative sphere for compliance with the laws issued by the Legislative Act, has ensured.
Analyse the possibility of a "vote by vote" count in Michoacán
According to the data provided by the PREP, the difference between the first and second seats of the governor's election is only 27 per cent, even without counting the votes for 879 of the 6 billion 74 total records.
The possibility of counting "vote by vote" is a reality with regard to this year's electoral process in Michoacán, where according to the data released by the Preliminary Electoral Results Programme (PREP) the difference between the first and second seats of the governor's election is only 27 per cent, even without counting the votes corresponding to 879 of the 6 billion 74 total records.
In this regard, the President of the General Council of the Michoacán Electoral Institute (IEM), Mary of the Llandal Angels Zaragoza, recalled that only a few days ago, last November, the electoral body adopted a series of guidelines to harmonise local norms with federal electoral reform.
As you will recall, Michoacán did not approve its Constitution or its Electoral Code of the State or its Electoral Justice Act, while the Congress of the State approved the reforms shortly before the end of the legal period so that they could enter into force in this electoral process and Governor Leonel Godoy Range omitted its publication within the time limits provided for in the Law of the Official Journal of the State, arguing that it had some objections.
On 9 November, the Supreme Court of Justice of the Nation (SCJN) resolved the constitutional dispute promoted by the local Legislative Power and described as "invaluable and illegal" the vote of the State Representative for Constitutional Reforms, although he does not have the right to "sanction them or vete them".
Interviewed about the possibility of "voting by vote", Maria de l'Angeles explained that the adoption of the relevant guidelines by the General Council of the EMI will allow for partial and total accounts of the vote by the local electoral body.
In this way, the partial counting of votes, of one or more electoral packages, may be provided in the assumption that: the results of the records do not match; there is no record of vote and record in the file of the case or does not open in the power of the President thereof; or, where there are manifest errors or alterations of the records.
In addition, the total number of votes received in all the electoral boxes may be obtained when there is evidence that the difference between the candidate alleged to be the winner of the election concerned and who has obtained the second place in the vote is equal to or less than one percentage point; where the request is made by the party representative and/or coalition which applied for the second of the candidates indicated at the beginning of the session.
The total count of the vote may also be made if, at the end of the ordinary course, it is established that the difference between the allegedly winning candidate and the second-place candidate is equal to or less than a percentage point, provided that there is an express request from the political party's representative, whose candidate remained in the second place, in which case the electoral packages which have been partially counted will be excluded.
It should be noted that in this situation is the choice of Morelia, where according to the PREP the difference between the first and the second place is only 0.16 per cent, although without counting the votes of 129 of the 923 total records.
