Immigrants are also net contributors to social systems, as they average 1% of the total budget in European countries.
For example, the International Labour Organization estimates that in Germany an immigrant who is 30 years old will make a net contribution of EUR 150,000 (less cost) to the public average budgets throughout his life.
At the beginning of his term of office, Nicolas Sarkozy wanted to go look for the growth points he missed "with his teeth".
These teeth, which deterred immigrants, had exactly the opposite effect.
